resources.name: riscv-disk-img
resources.documentation: A simple RISCV disk image based on busybox.

resources.name: riscv-lupio-busybox-img
resources.documentation: A RISCV disk image, based on busybox, to be used with the LupvBoard. Should be used with the 'riscv-lupio-linux-kernel' kernel resource.

resources.name: x86-m5-exit
resources.documentation: A simple binary which will run `m5 exit`. Compiled to the X86 ISA.

resources.name: x86-parsec
resources.documentation: A disk image containing the PARSEC benchmark suite, compiled to X86, built on top of Ubuntu 18.04.

resources.name: x86-gapbs
resources.documentation: A disk image containing the GAPBS benchmark suite, compiled to X86, built on top of Ubuntu 18.04.

resources.name: x86-npb
resources.documentation: A disk image containing the NAS Parallel benchmark (NPB) suite, compiled to X86, built on top of Ubuntu 18.04.

resources.name: x86-ubuntu-18.04-img
resources.documentation: A disk image containing Ubuntu 18.04 for x86. This image will run an `m5 readfile` instruction after booting. If no script file is specified an `m5 exit` instruction will be executed.

resources.name: riscv-ubuntu-20.04-img
resources.documentation: A disk image containing Ubuntu 20.04 for RISCV which will run an `m5 readfile` instruction after booting. If no script file is specified an `m5 exit` instruction will be exected

resources.name: riscv-boot-exit-nodisk
resources.documentation: A simple RISCV bootloader with Linux kernel 5.10. The early userspace includes busybox and the m5 binary.

contents.name: x86-linux-kernel-4.19.83
contents.documentation: The linux kernel (v4.19.83), compiled to X86.

contents.name: x86-linux-kernel-5.4.49
contents.documentation: The linux kernel (v5.4.49), compiled to X86.

contents.name: riscv-bootloader-vmlinux-5.10
contents.documentation: A RISCV bootloader kernel binary with linux 5.10.

contents.name: riscv-lupio-linux-kernel
contents.documentation: A kernel built with LupIO device (https://gitlab.com/luplab/lupio) drivers. Must be used when setting LupIO board workloads. Compataible with the 'riscv-lupio-busybox-img' disk image resource.
